Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6.Place the peppers over an open gas flame until black all over. Place in a bowl, cover with cling film and leave to stand for 1–2 minutes.Remove the peppers from the bowl and peel off the black skin, rinse underneath a running tap to get the remainder of the skin off. Remove the seeds and set the pepper aside.Place the shallot halves (cut-side down) along with the plum tomatoes and garlic cloves onto a baking tray and drizzle with the olive oil. Bake at the top of the oven for 30 minutes, or until the shallots are cookedMelt the butter in a large pan over a medium heat and add the roasted shallots, peppers and garlic.Add the hot stock and cook for 5 minutes.Blend with a stick blender until smooth and place back in the pan to warm through.Mix in the peppers and chives into the butter. Form into a long log shape and roll in cling film.Heat a large griddle pan and drizzle a little olive oil over the cut ciabatta, and toast either side for 1–2 minutes or until bar marks appear.To serve, ladle the soup into serving bowls and serve the toasted ciabatta topped with the pepper and chive butter on the top.The soup can be served hot or cold.